\# 🎬 PRD: Agentic Operating System for Film/Series Production
\#\# 📌 Product Name  
\*\*(TBD)\*\* – Working Title: \*Agentic Creator Studio\*
\---
\#\# 📖 1\. Overview
A modular, AI-assisted SaaS platform designed to guide individual creators through the complete lifecycle of a film or series project. It leverages AI to \*\*ask guided questions\*\*, extract \*\*original IP\*\* from users, and structure their ideas across pre-production to post.
\---
\#\# 🎯 2\. Goals &amp; Vision
\- Replace or assist traditional filmmaking roles using AI agents  
\- Preserve creative originality by using AI as a guide, not a generator  
\- Enable solo creators or micro-teams to independently execute high-quality productions  
\- Reduce third-party dependencies by using \*\*self-hosted open-source AI\*\*  
\- Fine-tune models over time using \*\*RLHF based on user inputs\*\*
\---
\#\# 👤 3\. Target Users
\- Indie filmmakers  
\- Scriptwriters and showrunners  
\- Creative producers  
\- Solo storytellers  
\- Small production teams
\---
\#\# 🧩 4\. Core Modules &amp; Features
\#\#\# A. Project Creation &amp; Collaboration  
| Feature | Description |  
|--------|-------------|  
| Project Workspace | Create and manage individual projects |  
| Fields | Name, Type (Film/Series), Description, Genre, Status |  
| User Roles | Admin, Writer, Editor, Viewer |  
| Collaboration | Invite teammates with role-based permissions |
\---
\#\#\# B. Creative Guidance System (AI Agent)  
| Feature | Description |  
|--------|-------------|  
| AI Q\&amp;A Flow | AI asks expert-crafted questions; user inputs responses |  
| Contextual Threading | AI remembers user input in creative flow |  
| Story Mapping | Convert Q\&amp;A into story structures (acts, beats, arcs) |  
| Originality Ledger | Track user-generated content vs AI structuring |  
| Agent Personalities | Script Doctor, Character Coach, Lore Builder, etc. |
\---
\#\#\# C. Pre-Production Toolkit  
| Element | Sub-Features |  
|--------|--------------|  
| Characters | Name, Role, Archetype, Backstory, Relationships |  
| Locations | Name, Visuals, Description, Events |  
| Script Builder | Rich-text editor, scene breakdown, versioning |  
| Timeline | Interactive story events or production calendar |  
| Research Hub | Links, files, notes, annotations |  
| World-Building | Encyclopedia, Magic, Species, Culture, Religions, Systems, Items, Philosophies |
\---
\#\#\# D. Production Support  
| Feature | Description |  
|--------|-------------|  
| Shot List Generator | Auto-create shot lists from script |  
| Storyboards | Manual or AI-aided visual boards |  
| Schedule Planner | Day-wise breakdown, roles, and dependencies |
\---
\#\#\# E. Post-Production Companion  
| Feature | Description |  
|--------|-------------|  
| Rough Cut Notes | Scene-wise notes synced with production logs |  
| AI Dialogue Polisher | Non-generative feedback on pacing, tone, and clarity |  
| Score Assistant | Suggests music mood tags or structures |  
| VFX Organizer | Shot log with notes, assets, and progress |
\---
\#\#\# F. AI System Architecture  
| Feature | Description |  
|--------|-------------|  
| Model Hosting | Self-hosted models from Hugging Face on cloud servers |  
| Fine-Tuning Loop | RLHF pipeline using user Q\&amp;A and project data |  
| Modular Agents | Domain-specific assistants for script, design, editing, etc. |  
| Feedback Loop | Upvote/downvote model suggestions, refine over time |
\---
\#\#\# G. Infrastructure Principles  
\- Use GPU-optimized hosting (e.g., LambdaLabs, RunPod, or self-managed Kubernetes)  
\- Integrate Ollama-like local model serving for testing/debugging  
\- Data privacy and encryption-first approach  
\- Open-source stack: LangChain, FastAPI, Postgres, Supabase, etc.
\---
\#\#\# H. Additional Features  
| Feature | Description |  
|--------|-------------|  
| Quick Search | Across all content (script, notes, characters, assets) |  
| Rich Text Editor | Markdown \+ WYSIWYG with comments and highlights |  
| Graphical Visualizations | Plot arcs, character graphs, pacing charts |  
| Export Options | PDF/CSV exports, shooting scripts, pitch decks |
\---
\#\# 🔐 5\. IP Ownership &amp; Data Privacy
\- All creative input belongs to the user  
\- AI suggestions are traceable and marked  
\- Projects are private by default unless explicitly shared  
\- Hosting and training data stays within your cloud infrastructure
\---
\#\# 🛠 6\. Tech Stack Overview
| Layer | Tech |  
|------|------|  
| Frontend | React \+ Tailwind / Next.js |  
| Backend | Node.js \+ FastAPI |  
| Database | PostgreSQL / Supabase |  
| AI Hosting | Hugging Face models on own cloud (Docker \+ TorchServe) |  
| Pipeline | LangChain \+ Custom Prompt Routing |  
| RLHF Training | TRL \+ HumanEval datasets from project flow |  
| DevOps | Docker, Kubernetes, GitHub Actions |
\---
\#\# 📅 7\. Milestones (MVP Roadmap)
| Phase | Deliverables | Duration |  
|------|--------------|----------|  
| Week 1 | Project creation \+ login \+ user roles | 5–7 days |  
| Week 2 | AI Q\&amp;A flow \+ character builder module | 7 days |  
| Week 3 | Story mapping \+ script editor \+ timeline | 7 days |  
| Week 4 | Research hub \+ world-building schema | 5–7 days |  
| Week 5 | Quick search \+ rich text \+ collaboration tools | 6 days |  
| Week 6 | AI model container setup \+ inference API | 7 days |  
| Week 7–8 | RLHF fine-tuning logic \+ feedback capture | 10–12 days |  
| Week 9 | Export, save, visual graphs, cleanup | 5 days |
\---
\#\# 🧠 8\. Future Enhancements
\- AI Voice Assistants for spoken idea capture  
\- Real-time co-writing experience  
\- Integration with video editing tools (e.g., DaVinci Resolve)  
\- Marketplace for hiring collaborators (opt-in human layer)
\---
\#\# ✅ 9\. Success Metrics
\- % of original IP generated through AI-guided flow  
\- User retention through phases (pre, prod, post)  
\- Time saved compared to traditional pipelines  
\- Quality score from peer reviews or festivals
\---
\#\# 📝 10\. Notes
\- This is \*\*not a generative tool\*\*; it&apos;s a \*\*reflective assistant\*\*  
\- User is always the originator — AI helps organize, structure, and accelerate  
\- Platform prioritizes \*\*creative autonomy and originality\*\*
